=== Stage 3 ===

[[File:Tour du Qatar 2015 (A3).jpg|thumbnail|right|Stage 3 route]]

The third stage of the race was a {{convert|10.9|km|0|abbr=on}} [[individual time trial]] at [[Lusail]]. The course followed a route that went past the [[Lusail Iconic Stadium]], [[Lusail Sports Arena]] and [[Lusail International Circuit]].<ref name=pcs-s4-route>{{cite web|title=Tour of Qatar 2015 - Stage 4|url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/race/Tour_of_Qatar_2015_Stage_3_Lusail-profiles|website=ProCyclingStats|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref> [[File:Luke Rowe CHB 2013 (Extra Cropped).jpg|160px|thumbnail|left|[[Luke Rowe]] (pictured here in 2013) moved into the lead of the young riders competition after stage 3]]  The riders were not allowed to use [[time trial bicycle]]s as would normally be allowed in an individual time trial; conventional [[road bicycle]]s were to be used instead.<ref name=cyclingnews-s3-gallery>{{cite web|title=Gallery: On the start line at the Tour of Qatar|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/gallery-on-the-start-line-at-the-tour-of-qatar|website=Cyclingnews.com|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref>

Favourites for the stage victory included [[UCI Road World Championships <U+2013> Men's time trial|current world champion]] [[Bradley Wiggins]] ({{ct|SKY|2015}}), four-time world champion [[Fabian Cancellara]] ({{ct|TFR|2015}}), [[Matthias Br<U+00E4>ndle]] ({{ct|IAM|2015}}) and [[Niki Terpstra]] ({{ct|OPQ|2015}}).<ref name=cyclingnews-s3-gallery/> Wiggins was wearing the [[rainbow jersey]] of the world time-trial champion in a race for the first time and was riding a road bike with modifications for better aerodynamics.<ref>{{cite web|title=Niki Terpstra upstages Bradley Wiggins and Fabian Cancellara in Tour of Qatar third stage|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-02-11/terpstra-upstages-cancellera-wiggins-in-tour-of-qatar/6084898|website=[[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]]|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=cyclingnews-s3-gallery/>

The first fast time was set by Lars Boom, who took 14' 33" to complete the course, before Matthias Br<U+00E4>ndle took over the lead with a time of 14' 22". Wiggins briefly took the lead with a time of 14' 13", but soon afterwards Cancellara went one second faster. Terpstra, however, rode eight seconds quicker to win the stage and take over the gold jersey of overall leader.<ref>{{cite web|title=Niki Terpstra takes ITT win and gold jersey in Tour of Qatar stage 3|url=http://velonews.competitor.com/2015/02/news/road/niki-terpstra-takes-itt-win-gold-jersey-tour-qatars-third-stage_360507|website=VeloNews|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=cyclingnews-s3-result>{{cite web|last1=Farrand|first1=Stephen|title=Terpstra nets double victory in Tour of Qatar time trial|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/tour-of-qatar-2015/stage-3/results|website=Cyclingnews.com|accessdate=10 February 2015}}</ref>

The race leader after stage 2, [[Alexander Kristoff]], finished 44 seconds behind Terpstra, 36 seconds off the overall lead. Other riders to lose significant time were [[Tom Boonen]] and [[Peter Sagan]]. Boonen retained his silver jersey, but Sagan lost his white jersey as leader of the young riders classification to [[Luke Rowe]] ({{ct|SKY|2015|nolink=yes}}).<ref name=cyclingnews-s3-result/>

