=== Stage 6 ===

[[File:Tour du Qatar 2015 (A6).jpg|thumbnail|right|Stage 6 route]]

The final stage of the 2015 Tour of Qatar started where stage 1 had finished, at the Sealine Beach Resort south of [[Mesaieed]]. It took the riders north to [[Doha]]. In Doha, the riders rode to the [[Doha Corniche]], where they completed ten laps of a {{convert|5.7|km|1|abbr=on|adjective=on}} finishing circuit.<ref name=pcs-s6-profile>{{cite book|title=Tour of Qatar 2015|date=2015|publisher=Qatar Cycling Federation|location=Qatar|page=87|url=http://velorooms.com/roadbooks/2015/qatar.pdf|accessdate=5 April 2015}}</ref>

After the previous stage, [[Niki Terpstra]] ({{ct|OPQ|2015}}) had indicated that his team would happily allow a breakaway to win the stage in order to deny [[Alexander Kristoff]] ({{ct|KAT|2015}}) the possibility of taking overall victory with the aid of the bonus seconds for the stage win and intermediate sprints.<ref name=cyclingnews-s5-terpstra/> A break was allowed to go away early, formed of [[Marcus Burghardt]] ({{ct|BMC|2015}}), [[Preben Van Hecke]] ({{ct|TSV|2015}}), [[Nicola Boem]] and [[Stefano Pirazzi]] (both {{ct|CSF|2015}}). They were able to build a lead of over two minute, but {{ct|KAT|2015|nolink=yes}} took up the chase to support Kristoff in seeking bonus seconds.<ref name=velonews-s6>{{cite web|title=Terpstra defends Tour of Qatar title|url=http://velonews.competitor.com/2015/02/news/road/terpstra-defends-tour-qatar-title_360771|website=VeloNews|accessdate=13 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=cyclingnews-s6-result>{{cite web|title=Sam Bennett wins final stage of Tour of Qatar|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/tour-of-qatar-2015/stage-6/results|website=Cyclingnews.com|accessdate=13 February 2015}}</ref>

[[File:Dunkerque - Quatre jours de Dunkerque, <U+00E9>tape 1, 7 mai 2014, d<U+00E9>part (A084).JPG|thumbnail|left|180px|[[Sam Bennett (cyclist)|Sam Bennett]] (pictured here in 2014) won stage 6]] The two intermediate sprints were both located on the finish line of the finishing circuit, on the fourth and seventh lap.<ref name=cyclingnews-s5-terpstra/> Burghardt, Van Hecke, and Boem were caught first, while Pirazzi was caught on lap 4. {{ct|OPQ|2015|nolink=yes}} attempted to place riders in the sprint to prevent Kristoff winning the bonus seconds; they succeeded in winning the sprint with [[Tom Boonen]], but [[Matteo Trentin]] was beaten by Kristoff to second place. Kristoff therefore won two bonus seconds, placing him nine seconds behind Terpstra. With a ten-second bonus available to the stage winner, Kristoff was now within reach of the overall win.<ref name=velonews-s6/><ref name=cyclingnews-s6-result/>

{{ct|OPQ|2015|nolink=yes}} then sent their rider [[Iljo Keisse]] into a breakaway alongside [[Gijs van Hoecke]] ({{ct|TSV|2015}}), with the intent of preventing Kristoff winning any more bonus seconds. Keisse won the intermediate sprint with van Hoecke second; they then allowed the peloton <U+2013> led by Katusha <U+2013> to catch them.<ref name=velonews-s6/>

In the final kilometres of the stage, {{ct|KAT|2015|nolink=yes}}, who had done most of the work throughout the day, were unable to maintain their position at the head of the peloton.<ref name=cyclingnews-s6-result/> After the stage, Kristoff admitted that his team was tired from their work during the week.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tour of Qatar. Alexander Kristoff is third in final classification|url=http://www.katushateam.com/news/press/tour-of-qatar-alexander-kristoff-is-third-in-final-classification|publisher={{ct|KAT|2015}}|accessdate=13 February 2015}}</ref> [[Fabian Cancellara]] put in an attack in the final five kilometres, but was brought back by the peloton led in particular by {{ct|IAM|2015}} and {{ct|AST|2015}}. In the final kilometre, {{ct|TTS|2015}} came to the front in support of [[Peter Sagan]].<ref name=cyclingnews-s6-result/>

[[Sam Bennett (cyclist)|Sam Bennett]] ({{ct|TNE|2015}}) was given a strong lead-out by his teammates. He was then able to follow [[Andrea Guardini]] ({{ct|AST|2015|nolink=yes}}), who launched his sprint with {{convert|200|m|-1|abbr=on}} to go.<ref name=cyclingnews-s6-bennett>{{cite web|last1=Benson|first1=Daniel|title=Bennett secures breakthrough win in Tour of Qatar|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/bennett-secures-breakthrough-win-in-tour-of-qatar|website=Cyclingnews.com|accessdate=13 February 2015}}</ref>  Bennett was then able to come past and take his first win of 2015, which he later described as the biggest of his career so far.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bull|first1=Nick|title=Sam Bennett celebrates biggest career win to date in Qatar|url=http://www.cyclingweekly.co.uk/racing/sam-bennett-celebrates-biggest-career-win-date-qatar-157469|website=Cycling Weekly|accessdate=13 February 2015}}</ref>

Kristoff finished 19th; he therefore failed to gain the bonus seconds he needed for overall victory and finished nine seconds behind Terpstra. Terpstra therefore won the Tour of Qatar for the second successive season. Kristoff won the silver jersey of the points competition, thanks to his three stage wins, while Sagan won the young riders competition. {{ct|OPQ|2015|nolink=yes}} won the teams competition.<ref name=cyclingnews-s6-result/>

